# Force source/text files to be treated as text by Git, and pin a
# line-ending policy for the project (Issue #112).
#
# Why `text`?
# Git auto-detects binary vs text by scanning the first ~8KB of each file
# for NUL bytes. A single stray U+0000 (e.g. an editor/paste accident) flips
# a file to "binary" — which silently disables 3-way text merging and turns
# otherwise auto-mergeable edits into "Cannot merge binary files" errors
# during git merge/rebase/cherry-pick. See issue #106.
# These explicit `text` attributes override that content-sniffing heuristic,
# so a rogue byte yields an immediate localized diff failure (and we notice
# the offending file) rather than a confusing merge surprise later.
#
# Why `eol=crlf`?
# Without an explicit `eol=`, the `text` attribute enables "auto-sensing":
# git's stat cache expects the on-disk form to match what the smudge filter
# produces for the index blob. When `core.autocrlf=true` is set (as it is
# globally on this dev box) and a file was committed *before* `.gitattributes`
# was added, the index blob is the raw on-disk form, the smudge filter
# "would" re-emit it, and the byte equality still doesn't satisfy git's
# normalization-aware stat cache. Result: a 224-line, 224-deletion "phantom"
# diff that is 100% line endings (`git diff --ignore-cr-at-eol` is empty)
# appears on every `git status`. Pinning `eol=crlf` makes the contract
# explicit (worktree MUST be CRLF, index blob MUST be LF), so after a single
# `git add --renormalize` the stat cache is consistent forever.
#
# Windows is the dominant dev platform for this project (see CLAUDE.local.md),
# so CRLF is the recommended form. Linux/macOS contributors will see `^M`
# characters in some diff tools, but most (IntelliJ, GitHub web) hide them
# by default. .bat files are also CRLF; .sh files are LF; everything else
# text in the project is CRLF.

# Kotlin — primary source language
*.kt          text eol=crlf
*.kts         text eol=crlf

# Build scripts
*.gradle      text eol=crlf
build.gradle* text eol=crlf
settings.gradle* text eol=crlf

# Python tooling (dump_analyzer.py etc.)
*.py          text eol=crlf

# Lua scripts (Mesen2 harness, tracer scripts)
*.lua         text eol=crlf

# Docs
*.md          text eol=crlf

# Config
*.json        text eol=crlf
*.yml         text eol=crlf
*.yaml        text eol=crlf
*.toml        text eol=crlf

# Shell / batch helpers
*.sh          text eol=lf
*.bat         text eol=crlf

# GitHub Actions
.github/**    text eol=crlf
